OTFLogger

INSTALLATION
------------

1. Download, compile and install the OTF library:
  http://tu-dresden.de/die_tu_dresden/zentrale_einrichtungen/zih/forschung/software_werkzeuge_zur_unterstuetzung_von_programmierung_und_optimierung/otf/dateien/OTF-1.8.1sturgeon.tar.gz
2. Simply run build.rb java

TRACE GENERATION
----------------

You can run muscle across multiple machines. After that each machine will create seperate otf files. Please copy them into one folder and use merge.sh script (consult the next section for details)

In order to enable trace generation you must place the `otf.properties` file in the current simulation directory

otf.properties attributes:

	generate_otf - valid values: enabled, disabled; Enables generation of otf files; default: disabled
	dir  - a directory in which otf files will be placed, default: otf_files
	debug - enables logging OTFLogger events to standard output; possible values on, off; default: off	
	time_limit= - time limit (in seconds) after which otf trace generation will be stopped; default 0 - continue generating traces until the end of application
	timer_close - possible values: enabled, disabled; Enables killing simulation after time_limit; default: disabled

Default values are used when otf.properties file cannot be found.

The otf.properties file is searched in the initial current working directory of the simulation.

